{"id":"orch-go-528","title":"Explore tradeoffs for orch-go opencode integration.","description":"Explore tradeoffs for orch-go opencode integration. Current problem: orch-go uses 'opencode run --attach {server} --title {name} {prompt}' which doesn't render TUI correctly in tmux. Python orch-cli uses standalone mode: 'opencode {project_dir}' then waits for TUI ready, then types prompt via send-keys. Options to explore: 1) Match Python's standalone approach, 2) Fix attach mode to work with TUI, 3) Hybrid approach, 4) Other alternatives. Consider: session management, server coordination, TUI rendering, complexity, reliability, feature parity with Python orch-cli.","notes":"workspace: .orch/workspace/og-explore-tradeoffs-orch-20dec","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T09:33:24.720422-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T09:33:28.18492-08:00","comments":[{"id":246,"issue_id":"orch-go-528","author":"dylanconlin","text":"agent_metadata: {"agent_id": "og-explore-tradeoffs-orch-20dec", "window_id": "@52", "spawned_at": "2025-12-20T17:33:28.185644+00:00", "skill": "architect", "project_dir": "/Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go", "backend": "opencode", "workspace": ".orch/workspace/og-explore-tradeoffs-orch-20dec", "beads_db_path": "/Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.beads/beads.db"}","created_at":"2025-12-20T17:33:28Z"},{"id":247,"issue_id":"orch-go-528","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing orch-go vs Python orch-cli opencode integration approaches","created_at":"2025-12-20T17:33:39Z"},{"id":249,"issue_id":"orch-go-528","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2025-12-20-design-explore-tradeoffs-orch-opencode-integration.md","created_at":"2025-12-20T17:34:41Z"},{"id":250,"issue_id":"orch-go-528","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Exploration - Analyzing 4 approaches: Python-style standalone, current attach mode, hybrid approach, pure SDK approach","created_at":"2025-12-20T17:35:33Z"},{"id":251,"issue_id":"orch-go-528","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Synthesis - Recommend Hybrid approach: keep current attach mode (works!) + add session ID capture. TUI rendering concern may be non-issue - code intentionally omits --format json for tmux spawns.","created_at":"2025-12-20T17:37:07Z"},{"id":252,"issue_id":"orch-go-528","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Design investigation completed. Recommend Hybrid approach: keep current attach mode (it works!) and add session ID capture. Key insight: TUI rendering concern may be non-issue - current code intentionally omits --format json for tmux spawns. Python orch-cli uses pure HTTP API for OpenCode, not standalone CLI mode.","created_at":"2025-12-20T17:37:35Z"},{"id":253,"issue_id":"orch-go-528","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Key insight: We CAN have both TUI and API! Sessions from standalone mode ARE visible via API. Recommend: spawn with standalone + send-keys (for TUI), discover session ID via API query, then use HTTP API for all subsequent interactions. Python does exactly this pattern.","created_at":"2025-12-20T17:50:50Z"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-5b9","title":"Fix: tmux spawn should not use --format json","description":"## Problem

When spawning in tmux mode, the agent runs with `--format json` which outputs raw JSON instead of OpenCode's interactive TUI.

## Current Behavior
```
opencode run --attach ... --format json --title ... "prompt"
# Outputs raw JSON lines to terminal
```

## Expected Behavior
```
opencode run --attach ... --title ... "prompt"
# Shows OpenCode's normal TUI
```

## Root Cause
`pkg/tmux/tmux.go:BuildSpawnCommand()` hardcodes `--format json`.

## Fix
- Remove `--format json` from tmux spawn command
- Keep `--format json` only for inline mode (needed to parse session ID)

## Files
- pkg/tmux/tmux.go line ~10","notes":"workspace: .orch/workspace/og-feat-fix-tmux-spawn-not-19dec","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-19T21:20:12.770066-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-19T21:22:38.592507-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-19T21:22:38.592507-08:00","comments":[{"id":86,"issue_id":"orch-go-5b9","author":"dylanconlin","text":"agent_metadata: {"agent_id": "og-feat-fix-tmux-spawn-not-19dec", "window_id": "@702", "spawned_at": "2025-12-20T05:20:23.098770+00:00", "skill": "feature-impl", "project_dir": "/Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go", "backend": "opencode", "workspace": ".orch/workspace/og-feat-fix-tmux-spawn-not-19dec", "beads_db_path": "/Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.beads/beads.db"}","created_at":"2025-12-20T05:20:23Z"},{"id":87,"issue_id":"orch-go-5b9","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing tmux.go to remove --format json from spawn command","created_at":"2025-12-20T05:20:30Z"},{"id":88,"issue_id":"orch-go-5b9","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Remove --format json from BuildSpawnCommand (line 80 in pkg/tmux/tmux.go) 2. Update TestBuildSpawnCommand to not expect --format json flag 3. Run tests to verify fix","created_at":"2025-12-20T05:20:47Z"},{"id":89,"issue_id":"orch-go-5b9","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Removed --format json from BuildSpawnCommand in pkg/tmux/tmux.go. Tmux spawn now shows OpenCode TUI instead of raw JSON. Tests updated and passing.","created_at":"2025-12-20T05:22:04Z"}]}
